<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Opening (bars 1-4): Gm/Eb/Cm territory. Open LH voicings (5th + octave). Light 2-note RH.
- Stanza 2 (bars 5-8): RH grows to 3 notes at phrase high points. LH fills out Cm/Eb fully.
- Bridge (bars 9-13): Bb major territory — brighter register shift, F5 appears in RH.
- Final (bars 14-16): Return to Gm close with full 4-voice LH. Final chord includes G5 in RH.
- A°(vii°) bars use A2-Eb3-A3 in LH — the tritone Eb expresses the diminished quality.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Bb4 common tone sustained across Gm→Eb (layer 2, bar 1, 4 beats)
- Bridge: bass walks Bb→G→Eb (descending by 3rds) in pedal (bars 8→9→10)
- Bar 11-12: Gm→Dm inner voice: Bb3→A3→F3 stepwise descent in LH
- Final V-i: A°(vii°) tritone on Eb→D resolves to Gm in bar 16

TEXTURE ARC:
- Sparse opening (pickup + bar 1-2): 2-note RH, 3-note LH. Somber Gm character.
- Growth through stanza 2: 3-note RH introduced, LH adds doubled root.
- Bridge peak (bar 9-10): Highest melodic register (D5-E5b), fullest chord voicing.
- Final cadence: Convergence to root-position Gm with G5 in RH — solemn close.
-->
